"{\"uid\": \"aljazeera.com-sports-2024-7-31-favourites-events-schedule-paris-olympics-2024-track-and-field-guide\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"When are the sprint races and who are the favourites?\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 53, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Where will athletics be hosted?\", \"from\": 54, \"to\": 85, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Al Jazeera explains.\", \"from\": 86, \"to\": 106, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 86, \"end\": 96, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Jazeera\", \"score\": 0.5904237177371148, \"rank\": 0.6897475897369809, \"text\": \"Al Jazeera\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Jazeera\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Jazeera\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Save  Share  Track and field competitions are arguably the jewel in the crown of every Olympic Games and the most eagerly awaited event for millions of viewers.\", \"from\": 108, \"to\": 268, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For hundreds of athletes, years of hard work and preparation will culminate when they step out for their respective events in Paris.\", \"from\": 270, \"to\": 402, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 396, \"end\": 401, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999993028723, \"rank\": 6.97060960409242e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Here's what you need to know about the competitions:  Track and field events include a wide array of running, walking, jumping and throwing competitions that form an essential part of the Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 404, \"to\": 606, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Races are generally held on the event's main track which is divided into eight lanes, while throwing events take place on a field surrounded by the track.\", \"from\": 608, \"to\": 762, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Walking and marathon races are held on the road.\", \"from\": 763, \"to\": 811, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Track and field competitions will get under way from August 1, starting with the men's and women's 20km race walks.\", \"from\": 813, \"to\": 928, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Preliminary and qualification rounds for other events will begin on August 2.\", \"from\": 930, \"to\": 1007, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The women's 100m final will be held on August 3, while the men's 100m final is scheduled a day later.\", \"from\": 1008, \"to\": 1109, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The women's marathon on August 11 will bring the track and field events to an end on the final day of the Games.\", \"from\": 1111, \"to\": 1223, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"All sprint and middle-distance races will be held on the purple track of the Stade de France in Paris and the field events will also be held at the same venue.\", \"from\": 1225, \"to\": 1384, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1321, \"end\": 1326, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999993028723, \"rank\": 6.97060960409242e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The marathon and race walks will be held outside the stadium in the French capital.\", \"from\": 1386, \"to\": 1469, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1454, \"end\": 1460, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.8976539939924325, \"rank\": 0.09106130328794354, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The world's top athletes will be vying for medals in these events:  According to World Athletics, these are the top-ranked sprinters:  Men:  Women:  India's Neeraj Chopra, who won gold in men's javelin in the last games, will come up against the world's current top-ranked athlete Jakub Vadlejch of Czechia in Paris.\", \"from\": 1471, \"to\": 1787, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1552, \"end\": 1567, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.9967139138148532, \"rank\": 0.0032969201488302104, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}, {\"begin\": 1620, \"end\": 1625, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India_national_cricket_team\", \"score\": 0.8415533013300313, \"rank\": 0.1845758182673743, \"text\": \"India\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India_national_cricket_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India_national_cricket_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1628, \"end\": 1641, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Neeraj_Chopra\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Neeraj Chopra\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Neeraj_Chopra\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Neeraj_Chopra\"}, {\"begin\": 1752, \"end\": 1766, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jakub_Vadlejch\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jakub Vadlejch\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jakub_Vadlejch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jakub_Vadlejch\"}, {\"begin\": 1770, \"end\": 1777, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Czech_Republic\", \"score\": 0.9998471468460153, \"rank\": 0.00015273409879102012, \"text\": \"Czechia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Czech_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Czech_Republic\"}, {\"begin\": 1781, \"end\": 1786, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999993028723, \"rank\": 6.97060960409242e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In men's shot put, American athletes Joe Covacs and Ryan Crouser will battle for gold.\", \"from\": 1789, \"to\": 1875, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1808, \"end\": 1816, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999986606046479, \"rank\": 7.010100176882163e-07, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1826, \"end\": 1829, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_DiMaggio\", \"score\": 0.9920408343095591, \"rank\": 0.007960157224086422, \"text\": \"Joe\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_DiMaggio\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_DiMaggio\"}, {\"begin\": 1841, \"end\": 1853, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ryan_Crouser\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ryan Crouser\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ryan_Crouser\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ryan_Crouser\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Qatar's Mutaz Barshim will be up against his closest rival and friend Gianmarco Tamberi in the men's high jump competition after both athletes famously shared gold in the last games.\", \"from\": 1877, \"to\": 2059, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1877, \"end\": 1882, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qatar\", \"score\": 0.9999999966532869, \"rank\": 3.346759698695166e-09, \"text\": \"Qatar\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qatar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qatar\"}, {\"begin\": 1885, \"end\": 1898, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mutaz_Essa_Barshim\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mutaz Barshim\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mutaz_Essa_Barshim\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mutaz_Essa_Barshim\"}, {\"begin\": 1947, \"end\": 1964, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gianmarco_Tamberi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gianmarco Tamberi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gianmarco_Tamberi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gianmarco_Tamberi\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The long-distance running events will offer stiff competition among the world's best athletes, most of whom will be from Africa.\", \"from\": 2061, \"to\": 2189, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Kenya's \\\"Queen of 1,500m\\\" Faith Kipyegon will look to complete a hat-trick of Olympic golds in her main middle-distance category but also in the 5,000m race in a bid to win a double in the same games.\", \"from\": 2191, \"to\": 2391, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2191, \"end\": 2196, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.135561934841728e-16, \"text\": \"Kenya\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kipyegon will undoubtedly be one of the biggest stars on the track in Paris.\", \"from\": 2393, \"to\": 2469, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2463, \"end\": 2468, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999993028723, \"rank\": 6.97060960409242e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Netherlands's long-distance running champion Sifan Hassan has entered the 1,500m, 5,000m and 10,000m races in addition to her favoured marathon category.\", \"from\": 2471, \"to\": 2628, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2471, \"end\": 2486, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.9954114025148014, \"rank\": 0.0036431130496453563, \"text\": \"The Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}, {\"begin\": 2520, \"end\": 2532, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sifan_Hassan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sifan Hassan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sifan_Hassan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sifan_Hassan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the women's marathon race, Tigst Assefa of Ethiopia, the world record holder in the category, will be one of the favourites for gold.\", \"from\": 2630, \"to\": 2766, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2676, \"end\": 2684, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"score\": 0.999986105590673, \"rank\": 1.389460160691167e-05, \"text\": \"Ethiopia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In men's competitions, Kenya's Eliud Kipchoge will look to sign off from possibly his last Olympic Games with a third gold in Paris.\", \"from\": 2768, \"to\": 2900, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2791, \"end\": 2796, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.135561934841728e-16, \"text\": \"Kenya\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\"}, {\"begin\": 2799, \"end\": 2813, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eliud_Kipchoge\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Eliud Kipchoge\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eliud_Kipchoge\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eliud_Kipchoge\"}, {\"begin\": 2894, \"end\": 2899, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999993028723, \"rank\": 6.97060960409242e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He will be running alongside compatriot Peres Jepchirchir andagainst longtime rival Kenenisa Bekele of Ethiopia.\", \"from\": 2901, \"to\": 3013, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2941, \"end\": 2958, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peres_Jepchirchir\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Peres Jepchirchir\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peres_Jepchirchir\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peres_Jepchirchir\"}, {\"begin\": 2985, \"end\": 3000, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenenisa_Bekele\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kenenisa Bekele\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenenisa_Bekele\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenenisa_Bekele\"}, {\"begin\": 3004, \"end\": 3012, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"score\": 0.999986105590673, \"rank\": 1.389460160691167e-05, \"text\": \"Ethiopia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kenya's Alexander Munyao will also challenge for the long-distance medals.\", \"from\": 3015, \"to\": 3089, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3015, \"end\": 3020, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.135561934841728e-16, \"text\": \"Kenya\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\"}, {\"begin\": 3023, \"end\": 3032, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexander_the_Great\", \"score\": 0.9993515007136374, \"rank\": 0.000535472484874148, \"text\": \"Alexander\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexander_the_Great\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexander_the_Great\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The preliminary rounds of selected track and field events and all medal events will be shown live via every country's respective rights-hold broadcasters and online streaming platforms.\", \"from\": 3091, \"to\": 3276, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Al Jazeera will have live text and photo coverage of a selection of medal events.\", \"from\": 3278, \"to\": 3359, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3278, \"end\": 3288, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Jazeera\", \"score\": 0.5904237177371148, \"rank\": 0.6897475897369809, \"text\": \"Al Jazeera\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Jazeera\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Jazeera\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow Al Jazeera English:\", \"from\": 3379, \"to\": 3405, \"entities\": []}]}"